The paper deals with structured output problems in computer vision, specifically facial landmark detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed model, IODA, is a deep neural network that learns both input and output dependencies, which suggests that it could also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of graphical models for modeling output structure, which could potentially place it under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
